  A Multiple auto crash along Bode-Saadu-Jebba road, Moro local government area of Kwara state yesterday claimed the life of one person. The accident happened yesterday. It was gathered that the accident was caused by excessive speed.  Spokesperson of the state Fire Service Hassan Adekunle said the “accident was a head-on collision that resulted in a fire outbreak which involved five heavy-duty vehicles (four trailers filled with different variety of goods and a petrol tanker.) “A man was burned to death  and all the involved vehicles too were affected.” He said, “Our firemen were able to minimise the damage by quickly putting out the ravaging fire.” 